\pard\s1\sb240\sa120{\b\fs44 {\rtlch\f1 \b \cf2 \fs28 Structural Elements\b0 }}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 Miscellaneous structural elements you can add to your document, like footnotes, endnotes, dropcaps and the like. }\par
\pard\s2\sb240\sa120{\b\fs40 {\rtlch\f1 \b \cf3 \fs26 Footnotes & Endnotes\b0 }}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 Footnotes}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24  and endnotes}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24  are automatically recognized and both are converted to endnotes, with backlinks for maximum ease of use in ebook devices.}\par
\pard\s2\sb240\sa120{\b\fs40 {\rtlch\f1 \b \cf3 \fs26 Dropcaps\b0 }}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs116 D}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 rop caps are used to emphasize the leading paragraph at the start of a section. In Word it is possible to specify how many lines of text a drop-cap should use.}\par
\pard\s2\sb240\sa120{\b\fs40 {\rtlch\f1 \b \cf3 \fs26 Links\b0 }}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 Two kinds of links are possible, those that refer to an external website and those that refer to locations inside the document itself. Both are supported by calibre. For example, here is a link pointing to the }{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://calibre-ebook.com/download"}}{\fldrslt {\rtlch\f1 \ul \cf13 \fs24 calibre download page\ul0 }}}{\rtlch\f1 \fs24 . Then we have a link that points back to the section on }{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "#_Paragraph_level_formatting"}}{\fldrslt {\rtlch\f1 \ul \cf13 \fs24 paragraph level formatting\ul0 }}}{\rtlch\f1 \fs24  in this document.}\par
\pard\s2\sb240\sa120{\b\fs40 {\rtlch\f1 \b \cf3 \fs26 Table of Contents\b0 }}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24  You can see the Table of Contents created by calibre by clicking the Table of Contents button in whatever viewer you are using to view the converted ebook. }\par
